body:
Picking up some of the capabilities presented in #3781 but with a builder-based approach. One of the biggest "wants" from #3781 (for me, personally) is to have a way of building modules where i can easily look up input ports and assign to output ports.

Example use:
```c++
auto modports = hw::ModulePortInfo( ... ); // (in0: i32, in1: i32) -> (out: i32)
auto module = b.create<hw::HWModuleOp>(loc, b.getStringAttr("foo"), modports,
    [&](OpBuilder&b, HWModulePortAccessor& ports) {
  auto res = b.create<comb::AddOp>(loc, ports["in0"], ports["in1"]);
  ports["out0"].assign(res);
});
```

No test included with this PR - didn't find it warranted to create a separate test pass just for this (and i plan to use it in an upcoming commit).
